cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a new convolutional neural network architecture that uses a parametric log based Dual Tree Wavelet Scatternet (DTWST) as the front-end. The paper focuses on improving the training of the network and demonstrates its efficiency on image classification tasks using CIFAR-10 and Caltech-101 datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of the DTWST as a feature extractor, which is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on image datasets, which is relevant to sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
